-- Inter RAO May Buy Enel’s Maritza Power Plant, Messaggero Says
-- B y   A r m o r e l   K e n n a
-- 2010-10-07T07:40:01Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-10-07/inter-rao-may-buy-enel-s-maritza-power-plant-in-bulgaria-messaggero-says.html
OAO Inter RAO UES  may buy the Maritza
power plant in Bulgaria controlled by Italy’s  Enel SpA , daily Il
Messaggero reported, without saying where it got the
information.  Inter RAO may be the leading candidate among five bidders
interested in Maritza, according to the Italian newspaper. Enel,
advised by Deutsche Bank AG, wants to get 600 million euros
($839 million) from the sale and talks are at advanced stage, Il
Messaggero reported.  EVN AG, AES Corp, International Power Plc and CEZ AS are
also interested in the plant, the daily reported.  To contact the reporter on this story:
 Armorel Kenna  in Milan at 
 akenna@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Celeste Perri at   cperri@bloomberg.net  